  "photo_url": "https://ulab.edu.bd/sites/default/files/styles/faculty_avatar/public/images/faculty/Khozaima_.jpg?itok=IGvsBiJ0",
  "bio_raw": "Mr. Khozaima Fatehali Ziauddin is an Adjunct Faculty in the School of Business at ULAB. He got his Twelfth Grade Certificate as well as his Bachelor’s Degree from Shimer College, USA/Oxford University, England where he was an Honor’s Scholar and from where he passed out with distinction. He got his Master’s Degree from North South University (NSU) in English in TESOL in 2012. He got the Vice Chancellor’s Gold Medal from NSU for maintaining a perfect CGPA of 4.0.\nHe joined the family business in 1983 and winded up his business in 2009. Since then, he has trained teachers at Scholastica, Sunbeams and Australian International School. Moreover, he has trained Managers of EBL and AB Bank. Also, he has conducted Business English and Business Communication Courses at ActionAid Bangladesh, WaterAid, Oxfam, FHI International, Grameen Phone, Independent University of Bangladesh (IUB) and at Bay and Trust Alliance. Presently, he teaches at ULAB, ActionAid Bangladesh, EMK Center and SPEED.\nHe specializes in teaching, conducting and designing English pronunciation and English communication courses and workshops along with career planning to help students develop their critical thinking, leadership skills, communication skills, etc. which are crucial to be employable in the fast growing and changing job market.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Business Communication, English Pronunciation/ Editing, Career Planning."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nDEGREE:\nMaster of Arts (English) with Thesis\nNorth South University, Dhaka.\n2012\nCONCENTRATION:\nTESOL (Teaching English to Speakers of Other Languages)\nRESULT:\nCGPA -\n4.00/4.00 scale.\nFirst Class\nDEGREE:\nBachelor in Humanities with Distinction\nShimer College, USA.\n1983\nCONCENTRATION:\nEnglish Literature\nRESULT:\nCGPA -\n3.68/ 4.00 scale.\nFirst Class\nDEGREE:\nExchange Program\nOxford University, England\n1982\nDEGREE:\nTwelfth Grade Certificate\nShimer College, USA.\n1981"
